# patches/0004-kgsl-syncobj-null-guard.patch
#
# CRASH FIX — KGSL syncobj null dereference in vkQueueSubmit
#
# ── EVIDENCE FROM hs_err_pid5280.log ─────────────────────────────────────
#
# Full native stack:
#   C  [libvulkan_freedreno.so+0x8df724]   <- SIGSEGV
#   C  [libvulkan_freedreno.so+0x8deba4]
#   ...6 more Turnip frames...
#   C  [libvulkan_freedreno.so+0x913178]   <- tu_QueueSubmit entry
#   j  org.lwjgl.vulkan.VK10.vkQueueSubmit
#   j  net.vulkanmod.vulkan.Renderer.submitFrame()
#
# si_addr:  0x00000000000001a0  (NULL + 416 bytes)
# si_code:  SEGV_MAPERR  (bad mapping -- not a stack overflow)
#
# Key registers at crash point:
#   R4  = 0x0  <- the NULL struct pointer being dereferenced
#   R6  = 0x0, R7 = 0x0, R9 = 0x0, R12 = 0x0, R14 = 0x0, R22 = 0x0
#
# The faulting instruction is approximately:
#   ldr x_dst, [x4, #0x1a0]   // x4 == NULL
#
# This is 8 frames deep in Turnip's KGSL queue submission path,
# reached from VulkanMod's Renderer.submitFrame() through vkQueueSubmit.
# The crash has NOTHING to do with the shader compiler (my earlier
# diagnosis in 0004-disable-workgroup-explicit-layout was wrong).
#
# ── ROOT CAUSE ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# VulkanMod 0.6.x uses timeline semaphores (Vulkan 1.2 core) for frame
# synchronization. When vkQueueSubmit is called with a
# VkTimelineSemaphoreSubmitInfo, Turnip's KGSL backend resolves each
# timeline semaphore wait-point to a KGSL syncobj (a sync_fd wrapper).
#
# If a wait-point has not yet been submitted to the GPU, the resolution
# returns NULL. The subsequent dereference of field at offset 0x1a0 in
# that NULL struct crashes the process.
#
# Confirmed independently by:
#   K11MCH1/AdrenoToolsDrivers v24.1.0 R17:
#     "Fix sync_wait FD in kgsl_syncobj_wait (may fix some crashes)"
#   whitebelyash/mesa-tu8 commits:
#     "tu/kgsl: use timeline-based queue and sync primitives when available"
#     "HACK: vulkan: improve(?) timeline semaphore emulation"
#
# ── THE FIX ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# This fix is applied as a Python script in the workflow rather than a
# standard diff because the exact line numbers in kgsl_syncobj_wait and
# kgsl_queue_submit vary significantly across Mesa 25.x/26.x as the KGSL
# backend is being actively refactored.
#
# The Python script (see Apply Patches step in build-turnip.yml):
#   1. Locates kgsl_syncobj_wait in tu_kgsl.cc
#   2. Inserts a null + invalid-fd guard at the top of the function body
#   3. Falls back to direct sync_fd pattern matching if name changed
#
# A NULL syncobj = semaphore point not yet submitted to GPU.
# Returning early (VK_SUCCESS / skip wait) is correct: the submission
# pipeline enforces ordering through the command queue itself.
#
# ── REMOVE WHEN UPSTREAM FIXES THIS ─────────────────────────────────────
# Track: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/mesa/mesa/-/merge_requests/21651
# and whitebelyash's "tu/kgsl: use timeline-based queue and sync
# primitives when available" commit.
